Data is stored in VARIABLES.

Variables are like storage boxes where you can put the data you want to store.

When you, the programmer, create a variable, the computer reserves a space for it in computer memory.  

In this case, the computer will create an empty box in one of the lockers it's already dedicated for your program. 

Variables are stored in specific locations in computer memory. 

Variables have different types. 

Variables have names.

